{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17655433","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17655433"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T22:03:49+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T22:03:49+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18665"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18665","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18665"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.09,0.27,0.09,0.5,0.05]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11397"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"77497"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11397","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11397"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18665"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63009"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4931"},{"type":"tags","id":"4932"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"7273"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"26410"},{"type":"contributions","id":"26617"},{"type":"contributions","id":"26640"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"77497","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/77497"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThe mentalis is a paired muscle of facial expression that contributes to movements of the lower lip and chin during various facial expressions.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the primary action of the mentalis muscle?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Draws the lower lip laterally","Depresses the lower lip","Flattens the chin","Elevates and protrudes the lower lip","Retracts the corners of the mouth"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eelevating and protruding the lower lip\u003C/strong\u003E action occurs when the mentalis muscle contracts. This muscle attaches to the mandibular incisive fossa superiorly and the skin of the chin inferiorly (Image). Its contraction creates characteristic dimpling of the chin skin while pushing the lower lip upward and forward.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDraws the lower lip laterally\u003C/strong\u003E - This action is performed by the depressor anguli oris, which pulls the corner of the mouth downward and laterally\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDepresses the lower lip\u003C/strong\u003E - The depressor labii inferioris is responsible for pulling the lower lip downward\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFlattens the chin\u003C/strong\u003E - Contraction of the mentalis creates dimpling rather than flattening of the chin skin\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERetracts the corners of the mouth\u003C/strong\u003E - The buccinator muscle performs this action during movements like whistling\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe mentalis contributes to expressions such as doubt, pouting, or displeasure. Like other muscles of facial expression, it receives its motor innervation from the marginal mandibular branch of the facial nerve.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The mentalis muscle connects the mandibular incisive fossa to the skin of the chin, creating chin dimpling when contracted.","The primary function of the mentalis muscle is elevation and protrusion of the lower lip during facial expressions.","The marginal mandibular branch of the facial nerve provides motor innervation to the mentalis muscle."],"references":["Netter FH. Netter Atlas of Human Anatomy: A Regional Approach with Latin Terminology. Eighth edition. Elsevier; 2022.","\u201cMentalis frontal\u201d by Anatomography\u00a0is licensed under\u00a0Creative Commons Attribution-Share Alike 2.1 jp Unported license. (https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/2.1/jp/deed.en). \u003Chttps://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Mentalis_frontal.png\u003E"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63009"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18665"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"21425"}]}}},{"type":"media","id":"21425","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/21425"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/HDmoIeQlhFjeHPtwLTY1KqI0rx8VAY.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/HDmoIeQlhFjeHPtwLTY1KqI0rx8VAY.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":640,"height":640}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63009","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/63009"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-07T10:11:30+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-07T10:12:06+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11397"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"77497"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationship